From: Avery Felts <averyfelts@Averys-MacBook-Air.local>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 09:51:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] gem: preserve failed shadow snapshot errors

When a legacy i386 page snapshot fails, retain that exact memory error
instead of overwriting it with a metadata-only validation result. Continue
through the common fault path so restartable REP instructions still commit
their completed iterations before reporting the failing page.
---
 blink/gem_embed.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/blink/gem_embed.c b/blink/gem_embed.c
--- a/blink/gem_embed.c
+++ b/blink/gem_embed.c
@@ -674,7 +674,8 @@ struct blink_gem_result blink_gem_machine_step(struct blink_gem_machine* g,
           return r;
         }
       }
-      error = g->cb.validate(g->opaque, m->faultaddr, 1, r.access);
+      if (!error)
+        error = g->cb.validate(g->opaque, m->faultaddr, 1, r.access);
       r.outcome = BLINK_GEM_MEMORY_FAULT;
       r.memory_error = error;
       if (restartable_rep) {
